CRAY CTI BUILDME

Package version is specified in the definitions.py file, via the PACKAGE_BRANCH variable

To build RPM run the following command:

  To build a package from a specific CTI build:
    Use -b flag followed by install path
      ./package_cti -b ../install

  To build to temporary/local directory:
    Use the -t flag as the last arg
      ./package_cti -b ../install -t

  To package and deploy to pkgs dir:
    Exclude the -t flag
      ./package_cti -b ../install

  To package the latest build to pkgs dir:
    Exclude the -b flag and install path
      ./package_cti

  To package a final package to pkgs dir:
    Include the -f flag
      ./package_cti -f
